---
layout: default
title: "{{ date }} Daily Digest"
parent: Daily Digest
nav_exclude: true
date: {{ date }}
---

# {{ date }} Daily Digest

{% set scoring_model = meta.get('scoring_model') %}
{% set summarization_model = meta.get('summarization_model') %}

{% if scoring_model and summarization_model and scoring_model != summarization_model %}
> Generated on {{ generated_at[:10] }} | Scoring model: {{ scoring_model }} | Summary model: {{ summarization_model }} | Cost: ${{ "%.4f"|format(meta.cost_usd) }}
{% else %}
> Generated on {{ generated_at[:10] }} | Model: {{ meta.llm_model }} | Cost: ${{ "%.4f"|format(meta.cost_usd) }}
{% endif %}

---

<style>
.daily-nav-panel {
  width: 250px;
  padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  border-radius: 10px;
  position: fixed;
  left: 1rem;
  bottom: 1rem;
  z-index: 30;
  max-height: 62vh;
  overflow: auto;
  background: rgba(20, 24, 32, 0.94);
  font-size: 0.92rem;
}

.daily-nav-title {
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
}

.daily-nav-panel ul,
.daily-nav-mobile ul {
  margin: 0.35rem 0 0 1rem;
}

.daily-nav-mobile {
  display: none;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 0.55rem 0.7rem;
}

@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .daily-nav-panel {
    display: none;
  }

  .daily-nav-mobile {
    display: block;
  }
}
</style>

<aside class="daily-nav-panel" aria-label="Page navigation">
  <div class="daily-nav-title">Quick Nav</div>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#arxiv">arXiv Papers</a></li>
    {% if papers %}
    <li>By category
      <ul>
        {% set nav_ns = namespace(seen=[]) %}
        {% for p in papers %}
          {% set category_name = p.get('primary_category', (p.categories[0] if p.categories else 'Other')) %}
          {% set category_anchor = p.get('primary_category_anchor', category_name | lower | replace('.', '-') | replace(' ', '-') | replace('/', '-')) %}
          {% if category_anchor not in nav_ns.seen %}
          <li><a href="#cat-{{ category_anchor }}">{{ category_name }}</a></li>
          {% set _ = nav_ns.seen.append(category_anchor) %}
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </li>
    {% endif %}
    <li><a href="#hacker-news">Hacker News</a></li>
    {% if jobs %}
    <li><a href="#jobs">Research Jobs</a></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if github_trending %}
    <li><a href="#github-trending">GitHub Trending</a></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if supervisor_updates %}
    <li><a href="#supervisors">Supervisor Updates</a></li>
    {% endif %}
  </ul>
</aside>

<details class="daily-nav-mobile">
  <summary><strong>Quick Nav</strong></summary>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#arxiv">arXiv Papers</a></li>
    {% if papers %}
    <li>By category
      <ul>
        {% set nav_mobile_ns = namespace(seen=[]) %}
        {% for p in papers %}
          {% set category_name = p.get('primary_category', (p.categories[0] if p.categories else 'Other')) %}
          {% set category_anchor = p.get('primary_category_anchor', category_name | lower | replace('.', '-') | replace(' ', '-') | replace('/', '-')) %}
          {% if category_anchor not in nav_mobile_ns.seen %}
          <li><a href="#cat-{{ category_anchor }}">{{ category_name }}</a></li>
          {% set _ = nav_mobile_ns.seen.append(category_anchor) %}
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </ul>
    </li>
    {% endif %}
    <li><a href="#hacker-news">Hacker News</a></li>
    {% if jobs %}
    <li><a href="#jobs">Research Jobs</a></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if github_trending %}
    <li><a href="#github-trending">GitHub Trending</a></li>
    {% endif %}
    {% if supervisor_updates %}
    <li><a href="#supervisors">Supervisor Updates</a></li>
    {% endif %}
  </ul>
</details>

---

<h2 id="arxiv">📄 arXiv Papers Today ({{ papers|length }})</h2>

{% if papers %}
{% set content_ns = namespace(seen=[]) %}
{% for p in papers %}
{% set category_name = p.get('primary_category', (p.categories[0] if p.categories else 'Other')) %}
{% set category_anchor = p.get('primary_category_anchor', category_name | lower | replace('.', '-') | replace(' ', '-') | replace('/', '-')) %}
{% if category_anchor not in content_ns.seen %}
<h3 id="cat-{{ category_anchor }}">{{ category_name }}</h3>
{% set _ = content_ns.seen.append(category_anchor) %}
{% endif %}

<h4>{{ loop.index }}. <a href="{{ p.url }}">{{ p.title }}</a></h4>

**Authors:** {{ p.authors | join(', ') }}{% if p.affiliations %} | **Affiliations:** {{ p.affiliations | join('; ') }}{% endif %} | **Categories:** {{ p.categories | join(', ') }} | **Score:** {{ "%.1f"|format(p.score) }}/10

{% if p.figure_url %}
![{{ p.figure_caption or p.title }}]({{ p.figure_url }})
{% if p.figure_caption %}
*Figure 1.* {{ p.figure_caption }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{{ p.abstract_zh }}

---
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
{% if meta.get('papers_after_keyword_filter', 0) > 0 %}
*No papers made the final cut today. {{ meta.papers_after_keyword_filter }} candidates passed keyword filtering but scored 0 after LLM scoring — this usually means the scoring threshold is too strict or the scoring request failed.*
{% else %}
*No papers matched today's filters.*
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

<h2 id="hacker-news">🔥 Hacker News ({{ hacker_news|length }})</h2>

{% if hacker_news %}
{% for s in hacker_news %}
- **[{{ s.title }}]({{ s.url }})** ({{ s.score }}pts) — {{ s.summary_zh }} [[comments]({{ s.comments_url }})]
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
*No matching stories today.*
{% endif %}

{% if jobs %}
<h2 id="jobs">💼 Research Jobs ({{ jobs|length }})</h2>

{% for j in jobs %}
### [{{ j.title }}]({{ j.url }})

**Institution:** {{ j.institution or 'Unknown' }} | **Location:** {{ j.location or 'N/A' }} | **Source:** {{ j.source }} | **Deadline:** {{ j.deadline or 'N/A' }} | **Relevance:** {{ "%.1f"|format(j.relevance_score) }}/10

{% if j.salary %}
**Salary:** {{ j.salary }}

{% endif %}
{% for line in j.requirements_zh.split('\n') %}{% if line.strip() %}
- {{ line }}
{% endif %}{% endfor %}

---
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if github_trending %}
<h2 id="github-trending">⭐ GitHub Trending ({{ github_trending|length }})</h2>

{% for r in github_trending %}
- **[{{ r.full_name }}]({{ r.url }})** {% if r.language %}· {{ r.language }}{% endif %} {% if r.stars_today %}· ⭐ +{{ r.stars_today }} today{% elif r.total_stars %}· ⭐ {{ r.total_stars }}{% endif %}

  {{ r.description | replace('\n', ' ') | truncate(100, True, '…') }}{% if r.summary_zh %}
  > {{ r.summary_zh }}{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

{% if supervisor_updates %}
<h2 id="supervisors">👨‍🏫 Supervisor Updates</h2>

{% for u in supervisor_updates %}
- **{{ u.name }}** ({{ u.institution }}) — {{ u.change_summary_zh }} [[page]({{ u.url }})]
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

